title: Railworks TS2014 TaD  German Highspeed 3
description:
Our third scenariopack of the "German Highspeed" series, besides the first scenariopack for Trainsimulator 2014, brings you to the Hamburg - Hannover route. Seven prototypical ICE and IC scenarios on this interesting route await you! Get into the cab and enjoy the ride with speed up to 200km/h.

It's a very cold morning and you are in charge of ICE 1097, the ICE Sprinter from Hamburg to Darmstadt via Frankfurt. The ICE Sprinter services calls only at the most important stations, so during your shift you will only stop at Hamburg Hbf and Hannover Hbf.

Drive the Intercity Express 588 from the outskirts of Hannover to Hamburg, stopping at Harburg on the way.

You are coming from LÃƒÂ¼beck, via Berliner Tor. Proceed to track 8 and open the doors to let passengers in. During the stop change cabs in preparation to the travel towards Hannover.

TaD High Speed 3 - 5. ICE 886 MÃƒÂ¼nchen Hbf - Hamburg Altona
The ICE 886 is one of the few ICEs stopping at LÃƒÂ¼neburg. Drive it from Hannover - Hamburg on this beautiful summer morning.

TaD High Speed 3 - 6. IC 2379 Stralsund Hbf - Hannover Hbf
This train comes from Stralsund and you are driving it until it's final destination, Hannover, where you are scheduled to arrive at 19:57.

TaD High Speed 3 - 7. IC 2184 Hannover Hbf - Ostseebad Binz
It's early morning and the weather is very bad. You are in charge of the Intercity 2184 - Ostseebad Binz, and you will drive it until Hamburg.
